{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nStatic wiring tests cannot prove that an LLM criterion distinguishes concrete breakage scenarios from harmless silence or valid project customization. A balanced, repeatable evaluation is needed before the blocking project criterion is considered ready.\n\n## What\n\nAdd a project criterion evaluation corpus, add structural tests for that corpus, run the existing live evaluation runner, and tune only the project rubric if calibration exposes false positives or missed portability failures.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- `.rebar/evals/plan-review-project-portability.eval.yaml`\n- `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`, only for calibration-driven rubric adjustments\n- `tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py`\n- live evaluation of `project.portability`\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- core registry, verifier, or disposition changes\n- coaching move behavior\n- existing portability debt\n- adding requirements for client-agnostic wording\n\n## Approach\n\nUse the existing project eval override path proven by `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md`: `.rebar/evals/plan-review-project-portability.eval.yaml` resolves for logical criterion `project.portability`. Author this exact top-level contract:\n\n- `prompt: plan-review-project-portability`\n- `model: anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6`\n- `epochs: 3`\n- `gate: at_least(2)`\n- `coverage_threshold: 1.0`\n- one deterministic `emits_valid_findings` scorer\n- a balanced `dataset` plus a non-empty `gold_set`\n\nThe dataset contains exactly eight ids. Each must-fire case uses `expect: finding`, includes an inline `input` plan, and records `expected_counterexample` metadata with non-empty `plan_citation`, `alternate_shape`, `causal_mechanism`, and `observable_breakage` fields:\n\n- `PORT-F1`: reusable core adds `rebar landing` with a Gerrit-only push flow; alternate clients do not use this repository policy.\n- `PORT-F2`: reusable core adds Python-only review criteria; Java, Next.js, .NET, Ruby, and Terraform projects cannot apply them.\n- `PORT-F3`: reusable execution requires the macOS `security` binary; Windows, Linux, and BSD fail before work begins.\n- `PORT-F4`: remote MCP derives the target repo from `Path.cwd()` plus unrestricted local filesystem access; a server outside the checkout cannot find or read the project.\n\nEach must-not-fire case uses `expect: pass`:\n\n- `PORT-N1`: the plan is silent about portability and contains no incompatible mechanism.\n- `PORT-N2`: Gerrit-specific coaching remains in `.rebar/plan_review_moves.json` project configuration.\n- `PORT-N3`: an additive terminal-color feature is explicitly limited to the CLI and leaves library plus MCP behavior unchanged.\n- `PORT-N4`: workspace discovery accepts an explicit path and uses portable standard-library filesystem operations.\n\nThe `gold_set` contains all eight cases with matching `finding` or `pass` labels. Run each dataset case three times through `rebar criteria eval`. The release threshold is recall `1.0`, false-accept rate `0.0`, `agreement: 1.0`, per-case `stability >= 0.6666666667`, and Cohen kappa `>= 0.70`. If the threshold is missed, revise only `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md` and rerun; do not change the generic registry, Pass 2, or Pass 3.\n\n`tests/unit/test_criteria_eval.py` is the prior art for project prompt-id mapping, injected calibration, metric keys, and N-run stability. The new structural tests use the real eval loader plus `validate_eval_spec`; they use an injected solve function for deterministic metric assertions and never make a billable call.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on the criterion-integration child because calibration executes the activated project criterion and its authored rubric.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\nValidate corpus structure deterministically, then use the live criterion evaluation command for semantic calibration. Record the model, timestamp, run count, and aggregate metrics on this ticket so the external LLM result is auditable by the completion gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The project eval override resolves from `.rebar/evals/plan-review-project-portability.eval.yaml`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k override_resolution`.\n- [ ] The eval spec declares the exact prompt, model, epochs, gate, coverage threshold, and deterministic scorer specified in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k spec_contract`.\n- [ ] The dataset contains exactly `PORT-F1` through `PORT-F4` as findings plus `PORT-N1` through `PORT-N4` as passes. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k balanced_corpus`.\n- [ ] Every must-fire case carries all four non-empty `expected_counterexample` fields. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k counterexample_metadata`.\n- [ ] The must-not-fire cases respectively cover silence, project configuration, explicit surface scoping, and portable alternatives. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k negative_boundaries`.\n- [ ] The gold set labels all eight dataset cases consistently. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k gold_set`.\n- [ ] An injected perfect solve produces recall `1.0`, false-accept `0.0`, agreement `1.0`, stability `1.0`, and kappa `1.0` through the real calibration function. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py -k calibration_metrics`.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Three live runs meet recall `1.0`, false-accept `0.0`, agreement `1.0`, per-case stability of at least `0.6666666667`, and Cohen kappa of at least `0.70`; a ticket comment records the command, model, UTC timestamp, run count, aggregate metrics, and every case result. Prove with `.venv/bin/rebar criteria eval project.portability --runs 3 --output json`.\n- [ ] Any calibration-driven edit touches only `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`. Prove with `git diff --name-only origin/main...HEAD -- .rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md .rebar/criteria_routing.json src/rebar/llm` and confirm the only calibration edit is the project prompt.\n- [ ] The final project rubric retains every structural marker owned by `immune-floury-toad`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py tests/unit/test_project_portability_eval.py`.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784166199484859001,"uuid":"ca0194a8-f473-47ba-8c6a-0db6a62f0d16"}